Feet inward.

112
00:07:24,390 --> 00:07:25,240
Feet inward first.

113
00:07:25,240 --> 00:07:26,000
Skate forward.

114
00:07:26,480 --> 00:07:27,190
Skate.

115
00:07:27,190 --> 00:07:28,040
Forward.

116
00:07:29,560 --> 00:07:31,070
Why aren't we moving?

117
00:07:31,720 --> 00:07:32,190
No, no.

118
00:07:32,190 --> 00:07:33,310
Feet outward.

119
00:07:33,310 --> 00:07:33,750
Yes, yes.

120
00:07:33,750 --> 00:07:34,360
Feet outward.

121
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:37,750
Why aren't we moving?

122
00:07:38,070 --> 00:07:38,600
I know.

123
00:07:38,600 --> 00:07:39,510
Lean forward.

124
00:07:39,510 --> 00:07:40,830
You'll move if you lean forward.

125
00:07:40,830 --> 00:07:41,240
You're moving...

126
00:07:41,240 --> 00:07:42,630
Wait a minute.

127
00:07:43,270 --> 00:07:44,040
Hey,

128
00:07:44,040 --> 00:07:45,680
are you sure you can teach me?

129
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:46,000
Besides,

130
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:47,920
we haven't been moving at all.

131
00:07:47,920 --> 00:07:48,920
Of course I can teach you.

132
00:07:48,920 --> 00:07:50,430
I learned it specifically.

133
00:07:52,270 --> 00:07:52,480
Forget it.

134
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:53,430
I can try it by myself.

135
00:07:53,950 --> 00:07:55,240
Remember the points

136
00:07:55,240 --> 00:07:56,560
I told you.

137
00:07:56,560 --> 00:07:57,630
Lean forward.

138
00:07:57,630 --> 00:07:58,120
Feet inward.

139
00:07:58,120 --> 00:07:59,040
Skate forward.

140
00:07:59,040 --> 00:07:59,630
Go.

141
00:08:08,830 --> 00:08:10,190
Good job, Jiang Yi.

142
00:08:10,480 --> 00:08:12,040
Did you train in secret?

143
00:08:12,040 --> 00:08:12,950
You skate well.

144
00:08:12,950 --> 00:08:14,510
He's talented in sports.

145
00:08:15,830 --> 00:08:16,720
Not really.

146
00:08:18,070 --> 00:08:20,000
Maybe I practiced
too many times in my head.

147
00:08:24,510 --> 00:08:25,240
Slow down.

148
00:08:26,310 --> 00:08:27,070
Good job.

149
00:08:27,070 --> 00:08:28,070
You skate well.

150
00:08:28,310 --> 00:08:28,720
Well,

151
00:08:28,720 --> 00:08:29,560
I should teach you.

152
00:08:29,560 --> 00:08:30,070
Come on.

153
00:08:30,870 --> 00:08:31,120
Wait!

154
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:32,030
What's wrong?

155
00:08:32,030 --> 00:08:32,960
I'm not ready yet!

156
00:08:33,440 --> 00:08:34,240
Relax.

157
00:08:34,240 --> 00:08:34,870
Your muscles are too tense.

158
00:08:34,870 --> 00:08:36,080
Wait a minute.

159
00:08:36,080 --> 00:08:36,550
My feet.

160
00:08:36,550 --> 00:08:38,270
My feet aren't inward yet!

161
00:08:38,270 --> 00:08:38,870
It's fine.

162
00:08:38,870 --> 00:08:41,030
Wait, wait.

163
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:47,360
Feet inward.

164
00:08:47,840 --> 00:08:48,240
Feet inward.

165
00:08:48,240 --> 00:08:48,910
I'm releasing you.

166
00:08:49,120 --> 00:08:49,600
Feet inward.

167
00:08:50,030 --> 00:08:50,510
Feet inward.

168
00:08:51,120 --> 00:08:51,600
Feet inward.

169
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:52,600
Feet inward.

170
00:09:09,720 --> 00:09:10,440
Look!

171
00:09:10,960 --> 00:09:12,150
I told you I could skate.

172
00:09:12,510 --> 00:09:14,030
I taught you well.

173
00:09:14,030 --> 00:09:15,750
I was the one who taught you.

174
00:09:15,750 --> 00:09:16,720
Slow down.

175
00:09:21,360 --> 00:09:23,120
Let Jiang Yi join in.

176
00:09:23,120 --> 00:09:24,440
Come on, Jiang Yi.

177
00:09:24,870 --> 00:09:25,960
Go have fun with them.

178
00:09:25,960 --> 00:09:26,840
Ignore me.

179
00:09:27,360 --> 00:09:28,600
Okay. I'm joining them.

180
00:09:29,030 --> 00:09:29,790
Go ahead.

181
00:09:30,120 --> 00:09:31,240
Be careful.

182
00:10:16,630 --> 00:10:17,670
Make way, make way.

183
00:10:29,030 --> 00:10:30,120
Are you okay?

184
00:10:33,360 --> 00:10:34,390
I'm okay.

185
00:10:35,030 --> 00:10:36,320
Are you sure?

186
00:10:38,240 --> 00:10:39,200
Yes.

187
00:10:39,440 --> 00:10:40,720
I'm perfectly fine.

188
00:10:40,720 --> 00:10:41,360
Look.

189
00:10:41,360 --> 00:10:42,480
I can skate this way.

190
00:10:42,910 --> 00:10:43,960
I'm fine.

191
00:10:43,960 --> 00:10:45,150
Go on, have fun.

192
00:10:45,150 --> 00:10:46,200
Slow down.

193
00:10:57,440 --> 00:10:58,870
Go easy, Mom.

194
00:10:58,870 --> 00:11:00,240
Bear with it.

195
00:11:00,510 --> 00:11:01,240
It hurts.

196
00:11:01,240 --> 00:11:02,870
Didn't you tell me this morning

197
00:11:02,870 --> 00:11:05,440
that you were going
to attend Stefanie Sun's fan meeting?

198
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:07,480
Why did you go skating suddenly?

199
00:11:08,440 --> 00:11:10,080
I suddenly didn't feel like going.

200
00:11:13,670 --> 00:11:15,390
I thought you hated skating?

201
00:11:15,390 --> 00:11:16,360
You're afraid of falling.

202
00:11:17,790 --> 00:11:19,440
If I'm afraid of falling,
how would I learn?

203
00:11:19,910 --> 00:11:20,550
Besides,

204
00:11:20,550 --> 00:11:21,030
if I can skate,

205
00:11:21,030 --> 00:11:23,000
I can have fun with my best friends.

206
00:12:12,120 --> 00:12:12,870
It's you.

207
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:13,960
Why?

208
00:12:13,960 --> 00:12:15,030
What do you want?

209
00:12:18,720 --> 00:12:19,600
This is for you.

210
00:12:25,600 --> 00:12:26,840
I had fun today.

211
00:12:27,150 --> 00:12:28,270
I won't take it.

212
00:12:28,750 --> 00:12:29,360
I'll use mine.

213
00:12:34,550 --> 00:12:36,600
Of course.

214
00:12:36,870 --> 00:12:38,080
If that's the case,

215
00:12:38,080 --> 00:12:39,750
you owe me a wish.

216
00:12:39,750 --> 00:12:40,910
I need to think carefully

217
00:12:40,910 --> 00:12:42,320
about what I want you to do for me.

218
00:12:45,750 --> 00:12:46,390
Sure.

219
00:12:48,390 --> 00:12:49,270
I'll leave now.

220
00:12:50,510 --> 00:12:51,120
Okay.

221
00:13:10,720 --> 00:13:11,320
Mr. Jiang,

222
00:13:11,750 --> 00:13:13,150
I've surveyed this case.

223
00:13:14,030 --> 00:13:15,550
During tomorrow's hearing,

224
00:13:15,550 --> 00:13:16,550
besides showcasing

225
00:13:16,550 --> 00:13:18,630
the initial concept design
for this game,

226
00:13:18,910 --> 00:13:20,510
you can also share

227
00:13:20,720 --> 00:13:22,320
your thoughts and emotions

228
00:13:22,320 --> 00:13:23,030
when designing this game.

229
00:13:23,270 --> 00:13:24,870
This way, they will be more convinced

230
00:13:25,150 --> 00:13:26,480
that the game is your creative work.

231
00:13:27,270 --> 00:13:28,270
Do you think

232
00:13:28,270 --> 00:13:29,600
there's a high chance
of winning the case?

233
00:13:30,270 --> 00:13:31,000
To be honest,

234
00:13:31,270 --> 00:13:32,840
getting evidence to prove plagiarism
is a challenging task.

235
00:13:33,630 --> 00:13:35,200
I've come across many similar cases.

236
00:13:36,030 --> 00:13:37,440
But that doesn't mean
we don't have a chance of winning.

237
00:13:38,960 --> 00:13:40,360
Tomorrow's hearing

238
00:13:40,720 --> 00:13:42,030
is the key to it.

239
00:13:45,630 --> 00:13:46,440
What if

240
00:13:47,200 --> 00:13:48,440
I don't show up?

241
00:13:48,790 --> 00:13:49,910
You must be there.

242
00:13:50,270 --> 00:13:51,360
You're the litigant.

243
00:13:52,080 --> 00:13:53,120
If you don't show up

244
00:13:53,200 --> 00:13:53,960
and we lose,

245
00:13:54,750 --> 00:13:56,910
our efforts will all be in vain.

246
00:14:07,510 --> 00:14:08,120
Yingzi,

247
00:14:09,630 --> 00:14:10,670
why are you spacing out?

248
00:14:12,150 --> 00:14:13,510
Dad, you...

249
00:14:14,150 --> 00:14:16,720
Please enjoy
the saxophone solo performance.

250
00:14:38,200 --> 00:14:38,790
How was it?

251
00:14:38,790 --> 00:14:39,440
Not bad, right?

252
00:14:39,440 --> 00:14:41,390
You're amazing!

253
00:14:41,750 --> 00:14:43,480
You can join a band.

254
00:14:43,870 --> 00:14:45,240
I'm already in a band.

255
00:14:45,240 --> 00:14:46,750
What is the name

256
00:14:46,750 --> 00:14:48,120
of your band?

257
00:14:49,030 --> 00:14:51,030
Well, Jonathan Lee and Wakin Chau

258
00:14:51,030 --> 00:14:52,440
have a band of middle-aged men.

259
00:14:52,440 --> 00:14:53,790
What was the name?

260
00:14:54,200 --> 00:14:54,960
Superband.

261
00:14:55,390 --> 00:14:57,630
Our band is Crossband.

262
00:14:59,720 --> 00:15:01,080
Crossband?

263
00:15:01,440 --> 00:15:02,670
When can I listen

264
00:15:02,670 --> 00:15:04,480
to Crossband's performance?

265
00:15:04,480 --> 00:15:05,200
Soon.

266
00:15:10,440 --> 00:15:11,270
Mom, you're back.

267
00:15:11,630 --> 00:15:12,150
Yes.

268
00:15:13,670 --> 00:15:14,080
Don't move.

269
00:15:14,510 --> 00:15:15,600
